-- Socar Aims to Be Among Top Five Global Traders, l’Hebdo Reports
-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m
-- 2011-12-21T15:48:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/socar-aims-to-be-among-top-five-global-traders-l-hebdo-reports.html
Socar Trading SA wants to be among
the top five trading companies in the world, Chief Executive
Officer Valery Golovushkin told l’Hebdo in an interview.  The Azeri commodity firm’s revenue will double to $38
billion this year from 2010 and it has increased staff in Geneva
to 86 from five in 2007, l’Hebdo reported in a pre-release of
tomorrow’s edition of the  Swiss magazine .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Giles Broom in Geneva at   gbroom@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net  